WorkItem.Description:
It's quite easy to change a column's visibility, e.g. myColumn.Visibility = Visibility.Collapsed. This works fine, and I can toggle the visibility many times without any problem.
However, I noted some strange behaviour when the header of the CheckBoxColumn contained an image. It would generate an exception that a child was already bound, crashing the app. 
 
A simple workaround was to remove the header image when Collapsing it, and adding it again when making it Visible, i.e.
 
private Image myImage;
 
myColumn.Visibility = status ? Visibility.Visible : Visibility.Collapsed;
switch (myColumn.Visibility) {
   case Visibility.Visible: 
      myColumn.Header = myImage;
      break;
  case Visibility.Collapsed:
    myColumn.Header = null;
    break
}
